thread.title: Queensland’s most clicked property did so well it made national top 10
thread.title_full: Queensland’s most clicked property did so well it made national top 10

author: Sophie Foster
title: Queensland’s most clicked property did so well it made national top 10
text:
A MULTI-MILLION dollar riverside home that went to market as a mortgagee sale was Queensland’s most viewed home online in the past year, landing so many clicks it also broke into the national top 10.
Realestate.com.au internal data for the period running from July 2014 to June 2015 found the six bedroom, four bathroom, five car space home at 302 Jesmond Road, Fig Tree Pocket was the sixth most viewed property nationwide - the lone non-Victorian property to break into the national top 10.
The property had been put to market by agents for the mortgagee exercising power of sale in October last year - eventually selling on May 9 this year for $4M, a full $1.5M less than its then owner paid a decade ago.
Realestate.com.au’s Alice Bradley said the Fig Tree Pocket home was a “six-bedroom mansion that looks like it could belong to a Kardashian”.
The building size was 737 sq m sitting on 0.72 ha (1.78 acres), with a self-contained guest cottage away from the home, a pool, 12m pontoon and plenty of space to put a tennis court in.
Agent Jason Adcock of Adcock Prestige said while the “mortgagee” element may have drawn some eyes, the property itself was “spectacular”.
“It’s got an American Hamptons’ style look. Properties in the vicinity go up to $15M (in value). The area is very highly regarded in terms of prestige property buyers.” 6 Benson Avenue, Toorak in Melbourne was the most viewed property on realestate.com.au this past financial year. Source: Supplied
Ms Bradley said the most viewed property in the country was 6 Benson Avenue, Toorak in Victoria - whose features included Iris Crystal Bohemia chandeliers and a waterfall window. It sold on May 19 this year for an undisclosed sum though a previous sale price in 2013 was $2.8M.
A former builder’s home at 8 Panorama Avenue, Lower Plenty , ran second nationally, with its “fresh air of the mountains, just a stroll from the Yarra”. Its sale price was not disclosed either but its fetched a previous sale price in 2007 of $1.1M.
A property at 29 Fisher Pde, Ascot Vale - which sold on July 9 for $2.55M - was third.
Originally published as Queensland’s most clicked property
